h3. Summary
Custom stylesheets are no longer overwriting *all* global styles and themes in recent versions of Confluence. Some styling such as margins and font-weight: bold are not overwriting the global styling. 

h3. Environment
Confluence Server

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Log in to Confluence as an administrator
# Go to a space
# Go to Space Tools --> Look and Feel
# Go to Stylesheets
# Enter custom CSS that changes styling for Headers 1, 2, and 3. An example of CSS is the following: {code}/* Generic Selectors */   

#content { font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", Times, serif; 
font-size: 14px;
}

div#children-section.pageSection
{
display: none;
}

.confluenceTable {
  margin-left: 40px;
  border-width: 4px;
  border-top-style: solid;
  border-right-style: none;
  border-bottom-style: solid;
  border-left-style: none;
}

.confluenceTh {
  border-width: 3px;
  border-color: grey;
  border-right-style: none;
  border-bottom-style: solid;
  border-left-style: none;
}
.confluenceTd {
  border-width: 2px;
  border-top-style: solid;
  border-right-style: none;
  border-bottom-style: solid;
  border-left-style: none;
}

ol li {
  line-height: 160%;
  margin-left: 10px;
}

ac:task-list ac:task {
