  margin-left: 18px;
}{code}
# Save the styling.
# Add a new page and add test text with headers 1,2, and 3.

h3. Expected Results
The custom font-weight: bold and margin-left: 10px properties should be overwriting global styling. 
h3. Actual Results
The bold attribute is not happening for headers 1 and 2 (it does do it for header 3) and the margin attribute is not happening for any of the headers.

h3. Notes
I have included 2 images to show the difference. This was working is working as expected in Confluence 5.2.

