As a Confluence user, I want to have a visual indicator on whether or not I am logged in. The indicator needs to be visible at all times, irrespective of my cursor position on the page.

Scenario: Quite often the user comes back to edit a confluence page after a time gap (say after lunch, or logging onto your machine first thing in the morning), and continues to edit a confluence page that was left in edit mode, there is no indicator to tell whether or not the user is still logged in to Confluence. Its only when the user hits "Save" button that the notification message is presented, prompting to log-in again... thereby losing the changes. This is a frustrating user experience.

Suggestion: Have a floating "Login-status indicator" that turns red or green based on the current log-in status. In case of an inactivity-time-out when the user is logged out by default, turn the indicator red so the user is signalled to log-in again before continuing to edit.

