Ampersand is not consistent across URLs within Confluence and it could cause Confluence functionality to break with different proxy configurations.

h3. *Feature that renders "&" symbol as "&amp ;" and breaks Confluence functionality.*
h3. 1. Attachment History that Return "Page Not Found" Error
{code}http://localhost:8090/confluence/download/attachments/360457/abc%2Bed%2Bsjdcn.xlsx?version=2&amp;modificationDate=1444745727902&amp;api=v2{code}

h3. *Features that retain the "&" symbol and work perfectly fine.*
h3. 1. Current Attachment Link
{code}http://localhost:8090/confluence/download/attachments/360457/abc%2Bed%2Bsjdcn.xlsx?api=v2{code}

h3. 2. Page History
{code}http://localhost:8090/confluence/pages/revertpagebacktoversion.action?pageId=360470&version=2{code}

h3. 3. Attachments From the Confluence Page
{code}http://localhost:8090/confluence/download/attachments/360457/abc%2Bed%2Bsjdcn.xlsx?version=4&modificationDate=1444745800102&api=v2{code}

h3. *Suggestion*
Standardise the URLs across Confluence. For example, retain the "&" symbol rather than switching to "&amp ;".
{code}http://localhost:8090/confluence/download/attachments/360457/abc%2Bed%2Bsjdcn.xlsx?version=2&modificationDate=1444745727902&api=v2{code}
(i) The URL works perfectly fine with only "&" symbol

