Our wiki uses labels to flag problem pages -- pages that are out of date, under discussion, in need of deletion, etc. Often, at a given moment, there are no pages for a given label, but we would like to explicitly see that fact on dashboard pages for the space. The problem is that, if we are creating such a dashboard page in anticipation of a label's use, the macro will complain and not let us use the undefined label.

I would like content aggregation macros -- in particular, the Page Properties Report and Content by Label macros -- to allow any valid label, including ones that are not yet in use.

